description: Set at the rear and one of only five in an impeccably-maintained block, this attractive mid-century villa delivers an exceptional low-maintenance lifestyle thanks to its quality enhancements, spacious outdoors to enjoy and ultra-convenient location. An ideal entry, astute investment or affordable downsize option, the home's flawlessly-presented interior comprises two large bedrooms with built-in robes both serviced by a modern central bathroom. Add to this a versatile front living room leading through to the updated kitchen/meals area complete with tiled splashbacks, modern cooker and Asko dishwasher. An abundance of natural light throughout, this vibrant villa also includes split-system heating/cooling, solid hardwood floors, internal laundry facilities, double blinds and original steel-frame windows. Complementing the home's impressive interior is a surprisingly large north-facing courtyard with handy storage shed and high fences for privacy, plus the added advantage of an undercover off-street parking space. Keilor Road trams, cafes and restaurants at the end of the street, it's also walking distance to shops and supermarkets, Woodlands Park, local schools (opposite Essendon North Primary School and zoned to Buckley Park College), as well as easy access to DFO and Citylink.
